# Integration: source first

When applying Harmony to **MUI** or **shadcn**:

1. **Read** [docs/PINNED_SOURCES.md](docs/PINNED_SOURCES.md) and open the pinned `harmony-styles/*.css` and `harmony-data/icon-manifest.json`.
2. **Read** [docs/MAPPING_PLAYBOOK.md](docs/MAPPING_PLAYBOOK.md) — identify which pass you are running and follow its checklist.
3. **Read** [docs/harmony-source-inventory.md](docs/harmony-source-inventory.md). If sections are still `TBD`, run [docs/GENERATE_INVENTORY.md](docs/GENERATE_INVENTORY.md) and update the inventory before claiming "theme complete."
4. **Derive** product themes and modes from **`tokens.css`** and the app's `html` class pattern — **not** from informal user lists in chat.
5. **Do not** paste designer starter reference-components components into the customer app as the integration deliverable; use them as **spec** only unless the user explicitly requests a hybrid.

After each pass, update **inventory §12** with mapped rows. After all passes, run the **harmony-completeness** agent, then the **harmony-verifier** agent (read-only).
